answers.q: comp where to plug e209 cable
answers.a: E209 is the E-number for heptylparaben, a synthetic paraben preservative (not permitted in EU foods); it isn’t a cable or plug.
In food labeling, E209 means heptylparaben, a preservative not permitted in EU foods; it doesn’t refer to Doctor Who.
